    ├── presets.js
    ├── FX/
    │   ├── delay.js
    │   └── reverb.js
    ├── arp/
    │   └── arpeggiator.js
    └── recorder/
        └── recorder.js



        Explanation:
Root Directory (Modular FM Synth v2/): Contains top-level files (index.html, README.md, etc.) and subdirectories (css, js, etc.).
css/: Holds the stylesheet (style.css).
js/: Main JavaScript directory with core files and subdirectories:
Core Files: audio.js, fmSynth.js, fullControls.js, keyboard.js, main.js, presets.js.
FX/: Contains effect modules (delay.js, reverb.js).
arp/: Contains the arpeggiator module (arpeggiator.js).
recorder/: Contains the recorder module (recorder.js).


Modular FM Synth v2/
│   Description: Root directory for the FM Synthesizer project.
│
├── NOTES/
│   Description: Miscellaneous notes (contents not specified in ls output).
│
├── README.md
│   Description: Project documentation and instructions.
│
├── framework/
│   Description: Possibly a placeholder or unused directory (contents not specified).
│
├── index.html
│   Description: Main HTML file defining the UI structure and loading the modular JavaScript.
│
├── css/
│   └── style.css
│       Description: Stylesheet for the synthesizer UI (keyboard, controls, etc.).
│
└── js/
    Description: JavaScript directory containing all functional modules.
    ├── audio.js
    │   Description: Initializes the Web Audio API context.
    ├── fmSynth.js
    │   Description: Defines the FMSynth class for FM synthesis.
    ├── fullControls.js
    │   Description: Manages synthesizer control UI (oscillators, envelope, etc.).
    ├── keyboard.js
    │   Description: Handles virtual keyboard rendering, MIDI input, and note playback.
    ├── main.js
    │   Description: Orchestrates initialization, event listeners, and module integration.
    ├── presets.js
    │   Description: Contains preset configurations for different sounds.
    ├── FX/
    │   ├── delay.js
    │   │   Description: Implements delay effect using Web Audio API.
    │   └── reverb.js
    │       Description: Implements reverb effect using Web Audio API.
    ├── arp/
    │   └── arpeggiator.js
    │       Description: Implements arpeggiator functionality for sequencing notes.
    └── recorder/
        └── recorder.js
            Description: Implements MIDI-style recording and playback with quantization.